        <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="70" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL">[quote]
Although a galant effort to help out casters i can already safly label the new focus items as a failure. The reason is simple.

We all know of that infamous little belt, the FBSS. It supplys a 21 percent haste to the wearer. NO MATTER WHAT LEVEL THEY ARE, NO MATTER WHAT WEAPON THEY USE. Where as the new focus items, mattering on their level of effect I, II or III. Will effect different level spells. That is rediculous. Especially if you look at the list of level III items that are already floating in, most are rare drops that a large majority of players wont see or be able to afford.

The level of effect should not dictate which spells benefit but rather how much the spells benefit. Level I should be something like 10%, level II should be 15-20% and level III should be 20-30%.

Verant took a great idea and totally messed it up. Petition! Send emails, tell verant what you think. I cant beleive this is what they call "balancing"

