        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Great observation! Why does everything for casters seem to be level based? From spells being level based now to focus items being level based. Why should a caster be penalized for leveling? This is exactly what these focus items do--penalize you for leveling. The example of the FBSS haste item is dead on. It give the same level of haste regardless of level. Tanks as they level strive to obtain items with higher haste rates. This is how caster focus items should be.</P><P>Verant is on the wrong track here. Seems they are following the level basic design of the summoned mage items. Focus items should work on ALL SPELLS REGARDLESS OF LEVEL. The only difference betten level I, II and III should be that the focus item increases in it's intensity and power. If a lvl 60 wizard wants to use a lvl I focus item while casting lvl 60 spells then he should be allowed to. The fact that a lvl I focus item will probably be very low level with lousy stats and certainly not an item that a lvl 60 would want to equip. Focus items would be inherently self-balancing if the appropriate power of focus is on a piece of gear that is relative to it's level.</P><P>Another excellent point was brought to light in another thread. Affliction(DOT) focus items do not increase the damage per second (DPS) instead they increase the duration of the DOT. These Affliction focus items should be increasing the strength of the DOT to give us a higher rate of DPS rather than more efficient damage over time. Basically these items will be useless to necromancers.</P><P>All I can say is that the Velious quest armor had better have necro friendly focus powers in the weeks to come. This stuff is the pinnacle of armor for most "real" necros out there that aren't in uber guilds. This armor took alot of work for my necro with faction, level and resists just for the priviledge to be able to fight in TOV to get these drops many of the