      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>web_trader</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> When I first looked at the list of focus items I thaught it made sense.  By putting high level focus effects on relatively low level items, they make us choose between the focus effect and stats.  Imagine a neck item with no stats except a level III focus effect.  Would you give up the stats for the effect?  Perhaps.  Perhaps not.  I was looking forward to having special use focus items.  Like the other poster, I was giving Verant way too much credit.</P><P>Everyone is looking at how hard usefull items are to get compared to their utility.  I think this misses the point.  The game is already designed such that a player must be very high level and in a very good guild to get the really great items.  That has not changed with the introduction of focus items.  Most focus items seemed to be designed for twinking.  Verant wanted to allow high level characters to be able to easily twink their low level caster characters in the same way they can do with their lowbie fighers.  The bottom line is that the new focus items are for your twinked secondary characters but will do little or nothing for your primary.</P><P>Frankly, Everquest is becomming very boring.  I just don't think I care much any more.  Being able to actually aquire a great item on my own would make the game exciting but all of these items have been nerfed out of the game.  I am left to mindlessly grind my way up through the 50+ hell levels.   Boooooring!</P><P> </font></td>
